Context.Comment: Enable the ROM code context for the peripheral(s) you want to use as boot device(s): this will restrain the pins choices to the ones recognized by the ROM code.
Context.Name: BootROM

Context.Comment: Enable the FSBL (first stage boot loader) context only for the peripheral(s) you want to use in TF-A BL2: this will limit the size of the device tree generated for TF-A BL2.
Context.Name: BootLoader

Context.Comment: Enable the secure context for the peripheral(s) you want to use in OP-TEE secure OS.
Context.Name: CortexA7S

Context.Comment: Enable the non-secure context for the peripheral(s) you want to use in Linux OS. Notice that the selected peripherals are also enabled in U-Boot device tree. Ensure that one U(S)ART is selected as ‘serial console’ among the ones assigned to this context : this choice will be applied in both Linux and U-Boot device trees.
Context.Name: CortexA7NS

Context.Comment: Enable the First Stage Boot Loader for the peripheral(s) you want to use.This context will configure the boot loader that will run in SYSRAM and load the Application in DDR.
Context.Name: FirstStageBootLoader

Context.Comment: Enable the Application context for the peripheral(s) you want to use. This context will configure the Application.
Context.Name: Application
